To set up a minimal version of the Vortikal server the following steps
are necessary:

1. Create a database using the DDL in the
   'src/sql/postgresql-schema.sql' (currently only PostgreSQL is
   supported, but HSQLDB has also been known to work in the past).

2. Set up the configuration. Configuration can be placed either in the
   ~/.m2/settings.xml, or in a properties file ~/vrtx.properties. 

  2.a Configuration using ~/.m2/settings.xml:

  <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
    <settings xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
              xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
              xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/settings-1.0.0.xsd">
      <profiles>
        <profile>
          <id>default</id>
          <properties>
            <!-- maven -->
            <maven.test.skip>true</maven.test.skip>

  	    <!-- vortikal -->
  	    <vortikal.indexStorageRootPath>[an empty directory for storing indices]</vortikal.indexStorageRootPath>
  	    <vortikal.jdbcUsername>[your JDBC user]</vortikal.jdbcUsername>
  	    <vortikal.jdbcPassword>[your JDBC password]</vortikal.jdbcPassword>
  	    <vortikal.repositoryDataDirectory>[an empty directory for storing files]</vortikal.repositoryDataDirectory>
  	    <vortikal.databaseURL>[your JDBC URL, e.g. jdbc:postgresql:my-user>]</vortikal.databaseURL>
          </properties>
          <repositories>
            <repository>
              <id>intra.usit.uio.no</id>
              <name>USIT Intra</name>
              <url>http://intra.usit.uio.no/web/maven2/</url>
            </repository>
          </repositories>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <activeProfiles>
        <activeProfile>default</activeProfile>
      </activeProfiles>
    </settings>

  2.b Configuration using ~/vrtx.properties:

  indexStorageRootPath = [an empty directory for storing indices]
  jdbcUsername = [your JDBC user]
  jdbcPassword = [your JDBC password]
  repositoryDataDirectory = [an empty directory for storing files]
  databaseURL = [your JDBC URL, e.g. jdbc:postgresql:my-user>]
  

3. Run the command 'mvn clean package' (standing in the project
   directory). If you run into trouble try 'mvn -U clean package'.

4. Start resin2 using the script in project-root:
   'sh resin-start.sh' (RESIN_HOME has to be set for this script to work)

5. You should now be able to access the web service on
   http:localhost:9322/ and the WebDAV service on
   http://localhost:9321/. Log in as 'root@localhost:fish'.

6. See the default configuration file
   'src/main/resources/vortikal/beans/vortikal.properties' for
   descriptions of the various configuration settings.
